---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy · Riviera & Ridge"
  description="How Riviera & Ridge processes your personal data. GDPR and Swiss DSG compliant. Data categories, retention, your rights, and third-party processors."
>
  <Nav slot="header" />

  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="legal">
    <div class="container narrow">

      <p class="draft-note">
        Draft — placeholders marked with [...] will be completed before launch.
        To be reviewed by a Swiss-law attorney (nDSG + EU-GDPR).
      </p>

      <!-- 1 Controller -->
      <h2>1 · Controller</h2>
      <p>
        Riviera &amp; Ridge<br />
        [First name Last name]<br />
        [Street, Postal code City]<br />
        Switzerland
      </p>
      <p>Email: <a href="mailto:hello@rivieraandridge.com">hello@rivieraandridge.com</a></p>

      <!-- 2 Data we collect -->
      <h2>2 · Data we collect</h2>

      <h3>2.1 — Contact &amp; enquiry forms</h3>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Data</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Legal basis</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Name, email</td><td>Reply to enquiry</td><td>Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR — pre-contractual</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Phone (optional)</td><td>Callback</td><td>Art. 6(1)(b)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Country / base</td><td>Logistics assessment</td><td>Art. 6(1)(b)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Number &amp; age of children</td><td>Care needs assessment</td><td>Art. 6(1)(b)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>"How did you find us?" (optional)</td><td>Marketing attribution</td><td>Art. 6(1)(f) — legitimate interest</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Preferred time / timezone</td><td>Callback scheduling</td><td>Art. 6(1)(b)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>
        We do <strong>not</strong> collect health data, diagnoses, or behavioural
        observations through this website. Details of that nature are discussed
        exclusively in the qualifying conversation (phone or video).
      </p>

      <h3>2.2 — Calendar booking</h3>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Data</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Legal basis</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Name, email</td><td>Appointment confirmation</td><td>Art. 6(1)(b)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Children's age, brief note</td><td>Call preparation</td><td>Art. 6(1)(b)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>Calendar data is processed by [Cal.com / Calendly] (→ Section 6).</p>

      <h3>2.3 — Agency placement forms (B2B)</h3>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Data</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Legal basis</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Agency name, contact, email</td><td>Placement coordination</td><td>Art. 6(1)(b)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Family profile (location, children)</td><td>Fit &amp; availability</td><td>Art. 6(1)(b)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Urgency, service tier</td><td>Prioritisation</td><td>Art. 6(1)(b)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>
        Agencies confirm upon submission that they hold their own legal basis
        for sharing contact data. Sensitive data (health, behaviour) is not
        collected via the form.
      </p>

      <h3>2.4 — Website usage</h3>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Data</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Legal basis</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Essential cookies (session, CSRF)</td><td>Website function</td><td>Art. 6(1)(f) — legitimate interest</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Analytics cookies (optional)</td><td>Usage understanding</td><td>Art. 6(1)(a) — consent via banner</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Calendar embed cookies</td><td>Functional</td><td>Art. 6(1)(a) — consent via 2-click</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <!-- 3 No sensitive data -->
      <h2>3 · No sensitive data on this website</h2>
      <p>
        Riviera &amp; Ridge does <strong>not</strong> collect health data,
        diagnoses, behavioural observations, or other special-category data
        (Art.&nbsp;9 GDPR) through this website. All information of this nature
        is discussed exclusively in the qualifying conversation (phone or video
        call) and is not stored digitally on the website or its connected
        services.
      </p>

      <!-- 4 Retention -->
      <h2>4 · Retention</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Category</th><th>Duration</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>B2C enquiries (no engagement)</td><td>6 months after last contact</td></tr>
          <tr><td>B2B enquiries (no placement)</td><td>12 months after last contact</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Engagement data (briefings, close-outs)</td><td>3 years (Swiss statutory obligation)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Calendar bookings</td><td>Per provider policy, max. 12 months</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Analytics data</td><td>[Provider-dependent]</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <!-- 5 Your rights -->
      <h2>5 · Your rights</h2>
      <p>You have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access</strong> (Art.&nbsp;15) — request a copy of the data we hold about you.</li>
        <li><strong>Rectification</strong> (Art.&nbsp;16) — correct inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
        <li><strong>Erasure</strong> (Art.&nbsp;17) — request deletion of your data.</li>
        <li><strong>Restriction</strong> (Art.&nbsp;18) — limit processing of your data.</li>
        <li><strong>Data portability</strong> (Art.&nbsp;20) — receive your data in a machine-readable format.</li>
        <li><strong>Objection</strong> (Art.&nbsp;21) — object to processing based on legitimate interest.</li>
        <li><strong>Withdraw consent</strong> — at any time, without affecting prior processing.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise your rights, write to
        <a href="mailto:hello@rivieraandridge.com">hello@rivieraandridge.com</a>.
        We respond within 30 days.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Supervisory authority:</strong> Switzerland — FDPIC
        (<a href="https://www.edoeb.admin.ch" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.edoeb.admin.ch</a>).
        EU — your local data protection authority.
      </p>

      <!-- 6 Processors -->
      <h2>6 · Third-party processors</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Provider</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Location</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Netlify, Inc.</td><td>Hosting, forms, deploy</td><td>USA (CDN global)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>[Cal.com / Calendly]</td><td>Calendar booking</td><td>[USA / EU]</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Meta (WhatsApp Business)</td><td>Messaging</td><td>USA</td></tr>
          <tr><td>[Plausible / Fathom / GA4]</td><td>Analytics</td><td>[EU / USA]</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>
        For US-based processors, data transfers are secured via EU Standard
        Contractual Clauses (SCCs) or the EU-US Data Privacy Framework, as applicable.
      </p>

      <!-- 7 Children's data -->
      <h2>7 · Children's data</h2>
      <p>
        Riviera &amp; Ridge does not collect data directly from children. All
        data about children is provided by parents, legal guardians, or
        authorised agencies, and is processed exclusively for the purpose of
        assessing and delivering childcare engagements.
      </p>

      <!-- 8 WhatsApp -->
      <h2>8 · WhatsApp Business</h2>
      <p>
        WhatsApp Business is offered as a convenience channel for scheduling
        and logistics. Messages are processed by Meta Platforms, Inc. (USA)
        under Meta's own terms. Detailed discussions about children take place
        in the qualifying call.
      </p>

      <!-- 9 Changes -->
      <h2>9 · Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this privacy policy to reflect changes in our services or
        legal requirements. The current version is always available at
        <a href="/privacy">rivieraandridge.com/privacy</a>. Material changes
        will be communicated via the website.
      </p>
      <p class="last-updated">Last updated: [Go-live date]</p>

    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</Base>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: var(--navy);
    color: var(--pearl);
    padding: 100px 0 70px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .page-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(34px, 5vw, 48px);
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .legal {
    padding: 80px 0 100px;
  }

  .narrow {
    max-width: 780px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .draft-note {
    background: #FFF8E7;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
    padding: 16px 20px;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 50px;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 26px;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin: 50px 0 20px;
    padding-top: 30px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  }

  h2:first-of-type {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  h3 {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin: 30px 0 14px;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 16px 0 24px;
  }

  li {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    padding: 6px 0 6px 22px;
    position: relative;
  }

  li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 16px;
    width: 8px;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--gold);
  }

  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 16px 0 24px;
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  thead {
    background: var(--navy);
    color: var(--pearl);
  }

  th {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 10px 14px;
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  td {
    padding: 10px 14px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(14, 26, 58, 0.08);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  tbody tr:last-child td {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--purple);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  a:hover {
    color: var(--navy);
  }

  .last-updated {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-top: 40px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .page-hero {
      padding: 70px 0 50px;
    }

    .legal {
      padding: 50px 0 70px;
    }

    table {
      font-size: 13px;
    }

    th, td {
      padding: 8px 10px;
    }
  }
</style>
